 inhaled corticosteroids);
 4. Any active infection requiring systemic therapy by intravenous infusion within 14 days
 prior to the first dose of study drug, including: HBV, HCV, HIV, syphilis infection,
 or active pulmonary tuberculosis.
 5. History of hypersensitivity reactions to murine protein-containing products, or
 macromolecular biopharmaceuticals such as antibodies or cytokines;
 6. Patients cannot guarantee effective contraception (condom or contraceptives, etc.)
